Package org.eclipse.gef.geometry.planar

Class Dimension

java.lang.Object
org.eclipse.gef.geometry.planar.Dimension
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Cloneable
public class Dimension extends Object implements Cloneable, Serializable
A Dimension represents a width and a height in 2-dimensional space. It provides various methods for manipulating the Dimension or creating new derived objects.

    • width

      public double width

      This Dimension's height. It is the distance of the y-axis that is stored in this Dimension.

      public boolean contains(Dimension d)
      Checks if the given Dimension fits into this Dimension. In order to fit into this Dimension, the passed-in Dimension's width and height have to be smaller than this Dimension's width and height, within the default imprecision (see PrecisionUtils).
      Parameters:
      d - the Dimension that is checked if it fits into this Dimension
      Returns:
      true if this Dimension contains the given Dimension
